This directory holds generated shell completion files.

Do not edit generated files by hand. Use:
  src/cmd/generate_completions.pl --format bash --out-dir src/cmd/completions/bash <tool>...
  src/cmd/generate_completions.pl --format zsh  --out-dir src/cmd/completions/zsh  <tool>...

From a configured build tree, the standard regeneration target is:
  make -C src/cmd completions

This target uses built OpenAFS binaries as the source of truth and refreshes
the checked-in bash and zsh completion files in this directory.

Some tools (for example, kas) require client configuration files and may fail
when run in a build tree. You can:
  1) Skip failures:
     src/cmd/generate_completions.pl --format bash --out-dir src/cmd/completions/bash --skip-fail <tool>...
     src/cmd/generate_completions.pl --format zsh  --out-dir src/cmd/completions/zsh  --skip-fail <tool>...
  2) Provide an alternate AFSCONF directory:
     src/cmd/generate_completions.pl --format bash --out-dir src/cmd/completions/bash --afsconf-dir /path/to/etc <tool>...
  3) Create a temporary minimal AFSCONF directory automatically:
     src/cmd/generate_completions.pl --format bash --out-dir src/cmd/completions/bash --afsconf-temp <tool>...

Installation:
  make install copies bash completions to:
    $(datadir)/bash-completion/completions/<tool>
  make install copies zsh completions to:
    $(datadir)/zsh/site-functions/_<tool>

Validation:
  make -C tests check-completions

The automated tests cover cmd --dump-syntax JSON output, generated file
syntax, and bash completion behavior for the checked-in scripts.
